                    <comment id="12560919" author="enorman" created="Mon, 21 Jan 2008 03:16:49 +0000"  >proposed repository-1.4.dtd file that includes the DataStore element definition</comment>
                    <comment id="12561096" author="efranqueiro" created="Mon, 21 Jan 2008 19:07:57 +0000"  >Shouldn&amp;#39;t the org.jackrabbit.useDataStore system property be documented in the wiki too? Because although in RepositoryImpl&amp;#39;s constructor it is asserted true in case the data store config is not null, in InternalValue it&amp;#39;s used regardless of the case. So if the data store is not configured but the property is true (which is it&amp;#39;s default value) then the processing in InternalValue is wrong. IMHO, this property should be removed altogether.&lt;br/&gt;
Regards</comment>
                    <comment id="12561243" author="tmueller" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2008 07:32:58 +0000"  >Hi Esteban,&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The system property org.jackrabbit.useDataStore is a &amp;#39;kill switch&amp;#39; to disable the new code in InternalValue and do everything as before (not using BLOBInMemory and so on). This property should never be switched off, except if there is a problem with the data store, and you want to check if the new code is to blame. I don&amp;#39;t think it is needed any longer, I will remove this property (and the old code) in the trunk.</comment>
